        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 6 at 5:11PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 511 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles southeast of Bingham, or 23 miles northwest of Carrizozo,
moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mainly rural areas of Southeastern Socorro County.

This includes Highway 380 between Mile Markers 35 and 51.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
